what is workspace in terraform?
Terraform, a workspace is used to manage multiple state files for the same configuration, allowing us to deploy the same infrastructure code across different environments like dev, staging, and production.

#Workspace related commands
terraform workspace list        # Show all workspaces
terraform workspace new dev    # Create a new workspace
terraform workspace select dev # Switch to workspace
terraform workspace show       # Show current workspace

🔹 When to use workspaces (and when not)
✅ Good for:
Simple environment separation (dev/test/prod)
Lightweight setups
Small-to-medium projects
❌ Avoid for:
Complex infrastructure differences between environments
When environments require different configurations or modules
Large teams needing strict isolation (use separate backends or directories instead)

🔹 Alternative approaches
Instead of workspaces, many teams prefer:
Separate directories (/dev, /prod)
Separate backends (different S3 buckets, etc.)
Using tools like Terragrunt for better environment management



